<H3> <TI>   Varennikov Calls Indictment `Fantasy' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94UM0249B Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 18 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 94UM0249B </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Item by Petr Karapetyan, KRASNAYA ZVEZDA] </F>
  [Text] On 17 February former Commander-in-Chief of Ground 
Troops Valentin Varennikov testified in proceedings in the case 
of the GKChP [State Committee for the State of Emergency]. 
  Calling the procuracy's charges against him in the plot 
against President Mikhail Gorbachev a fantasy, he declared that, 
being in Kiev on 18 August 1991, he did not present the 
leadership of Ukraine with demands for supporting the GKChP and 
instituting a state of emergency in western oblasts of the 
republic, nor did he assign any missions of any kind to the 
Commander-in-Chief, Black Sea Fleet regarding Belbek Airfield. 
Varennikov emphasized that "none of this was within my 
competence; I did not demand, I recommended." 

</TEXT>

