<F P=101> POLICY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Collegium Discusses PVO, MATS </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94UM0249A Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 23 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 94UM0249A </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Item by Russian Ministry of Defense Information and Press </F>
Directorate: "Russian Ministry of Defense Collegium Session"] 
  [Text] A routine session of the Russian Federation Ministry 
of Defense Collegium considered the question of the status and 
organization of alert duty in the air defense system. Colonel 
General of Aviation V. A. Prudnikov, Commander-in-Chief Air 
Defense Troops, gave a briefing. 
  The Ministry of Defense Collegium session also analyzed 
problems of further development of Military Transport Aviation 
in light of requirements of the "Basic Provisions of Military 
Doctrine" and Russian Federation Minister of Defense orders. 
Colonel General of Aviation V. V. Yefanov, commander of Military 
Transport Aviation, gave a briefing on this matter. 
  Results of the Collegium session were summed up by Russian 
Minister of Defense General of the Army P. S. Grachev. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

